🧠  SECTION 6: AI TUTORING LOGIC
How the AI tutor works — prompts, chunking, evaluation, and adaptation

6.1 Overview — How BRAUDLE Teaches
Every session follows this flow:

Document Uploaded  →  Text Extracted (PDF/Image)  →  Chunked into Sections
↓
Student Chooses Intent:
[ Teach Mode ] | [ Explain Concepts ] | [ I sabi am, give me quiz ] | [ Exam for it ] | [ Others... ]
↓
System Prompt Fixed Based on Choice  →  Groq API Called
↓
AI Interacts via SSE Stream  →  Asks Questions if teaching  →  Student Answers
↓
AI Evaluates Answer  →  Corrects Misconceptions  →  Moves Forward
↓
Session Done  →  Summary Generated  →  Score Calculated  →  Profile Updated

6.2 Document Chunking Strategy
Chunking is the most critical pre-processing step. Poor chunking = poor teaching. BRAUDLE uses a semantic-aware chunking approach:

Strategy	How It Works	Why It Matters
Target size	~500 tokens per chunk (approx 350-400 words)	Fits within optimal context window for clear explanations
Boundary detection	Split at paragraph breaks and heading boundaries first	Preserves logical units — AI teaches complete ideas, not half-sentences
Overlap	50-token overlap between consecutive chunks	Prevents AI losing context between sections
Metadata tagging	Each chunk tagged with: chunk index, estimated topic, page range	Enables progress tracking and session recovery

6.3 System Prompt Architecture
Every call to Claude is built from a layered prompt:

Layer 1	ROLE DEFINITION — 'You are BRAUDLE, a patient and encouraging personal tutor for students. You do NOT summarise. You teach, question, and evaluate.'
Layer 2	STUDENT CONTEXT — 'The student's current level is: {level}. Their weak topics include: {weakTopics}. Adapt your explanation depth accordingly.'
Layer 3	CURRENT CHUNK — 'Here is the section you are teaching right now: {chunk_text}. Teach this in 3-5 clear points. Use simple language. After explaining, ask one comprehension question. Wait for the student to answer before continuing.'
Layer 4	CONVERSATION HISTORY — Full messages[] array injected here so Claude has full context of what has already been taught and answered.
Layer 5	BEHAVIOUR RULES — 'If student answer is wrong, identify the specific misunderstanding and correct it clearly before moving on. Never skip a wrong answer. Never be harsh or discouraging.'

6.4 Quiz Generation Prompt
After teaching is complete, BRAUDLE generates a quiz using this structured prompt:

QUIZ GENERATION PROMPT STRUCTURE:

System: You are a professional exam question writer for students.
        Generate exactly {n} questions based ONLY on the provided content.
        Mix question types: 60% MCQ, 40% short theory.
        Each question must have: question, type, options[], answer, explanation.
        Return ONLY valid JSON. No markdown, no preamble.

User:   Here is the full content studied in this session:
        {all_chunks_text}
        Generate {n} quiz questions covering all major topics above.

Expected response: JSON array of question objects matching the Quiz schema.

6.5 Misconception Detection Logic
When a student answers a check question incorrectly, the AI does NOT just say 'wrong'. It follows this evaluation pattern:

Student Answer Type	AI Response Strategy
Completely wrong	Identify what they got wrong specifically. Re-explain just that concept. Ask a simpler version of the same question.
Partially correct	Acknowledge what was right. Pinpoint the specific gap. Clarify and ask them to complete the answer.
Correct but unclear	Confirm it is correct. Ask them to explain it in their own words to solidify understanding.
Correct	Confirm clearly. Give brief positive reinforcement. Move to the next chunk.

6.6 Adaptive Learning — How the Profile Updates
After every quiz submission, the system automatically updates the StudentProfile:

•	Questions scored < 60% → topic added to weakTopics array
•	Questions scored >= 85% → topic added to strongTopics array
•	Overall score < 50% → level stays or downgrades one step
•	Overall score >= 80% consistently (3+ sessions) → level upgrades
•	Future teach sessions inject weakTopics into the prompt — AI spends more time on weak areas
 
