⚡  SECTION 7B: AI ENGINE ARCHITECTURE (Groq + Hugging Face)
Model selection, SDK setup, and specialized task routing

7B.1 Dual-Provider Strategy (Zero Cost)
BRAUDLE uses a hybrid approach to maintain zero AI costs during Phase 1 by utilizing the free tiers of Groq and Hugging Face.

Provider	Models Used	Primary Role
Groq	Llama 3.3 70B, 3.1 8B, 3.2 Vision	High-speed reasoning, teaching, and OCR
Hugging Face	MiniLM-L6, Flan-T5	Zero-LLM cost classification and semantic matching

7B.2 Model Job Routing
Model	Job Description	Reason
llama-3.3-70b-versatile	Primary Teaching Engine	Deep reasoning needed for adaptive tutoring
llama-3.1-8b-instant	Fast Flags & Simple Checks	Low latency for casual interactions
llama-3.2-11b-vision	Handwriting/Image Transcription	Vision-capable for student note uploads
all-MiniLM-L6-v2 (HF)	Semantic Similarity Scoring	Evaluates short answers against correct ones without LLM calls
flan-t5-large (HF)	Fast Answer Classification	Efficiently categorizes responses as 'Correct', 'Partial', etc.

7B.3 SDK Setup (ai.service.js)

// Install: npm install groq-sdk

import Groq from 'groq-sdk';

const groq = new Groq({ apiKey: process.env.GROQ_API_KEY });

export async function callGroq(messages: Message[], stream = true) {
  return await groq.chat.completions.create({
    model:       'llama-3.3-70b-versatile',
    messages,
    stream,
    temperature: 0.7,
    max_tokens:  1024,
    top_p:       0.9,
  });
}

7B.4 Streaming to the Frontend
Groq streams tokens back chunk by chunk. The backend pipes this stream to the frontend using Server-Sent Events (SSE). The frontend displays each token as it arrives — exactly like a tutor typing in real time.

// Backend — Express route streaming Groq response via SSE

res.setHeader('Content-Type', 'text/event-stream');
res.setHeader('Cache-Control', 'no-cache');

const stream = await callGroq(messages, true);

for await (const chunk of stream) {
  const token = chunk.choices[0]?.delta?.content || '';
  res.write(`data: ${JSON.stringify({ token })}\n\n`);
}

res.write('data: [DONE]\n\n');
res.end();

