🤖  SECTION 10: INSTRUCTIONS FOR AI AGENTS
How AI coding agents should interpret and work on this codebase

10.1 What This Project Is
BRAUDLE is an AI-powered personal tutor web app. It is NOT a summariser, flashcard app, or chatbot. It is a full adaptive learning system. Every feature should serve the core mission: teach students effectively and personally.

10.2 Core Rules for Agents
•	Use JavaScript (ESM) for backend — use TypeScript for frontend only
•	Auth is Google OAuth ONLY — never add password fields, bcrypt, or manual registration logic
•	All API routes must have JWT middleware unless explicitly marked public (Google callback routes are public)
•	Never hardcode API keys — always read from process.env
•	All Groq API calls must go through ai.service.js — never call Groq directly in controllers
•	Chunking logic lives exclusively in utils/chunker.js — do not duplicate it
•	Every new MongoDB model must follow the existing schema pattern with timestamps: true
•	Use async/await throughout — no .then() chains
•	All errors must be passed to next(error) for the global error handler to catch

10.3 How Sessions Work (For Agents)
When an agent is implementing or extending a learning session, follow this logic:

•	1. Post-Upload: System prompts user for intent ('Teach Mode', 'Explain concepts', 'I sabi am, give me quiz', 'Exam', or 'Others')
•	2. Session starts — load document chunks from DB and initialize based on chosen mode
•	3. Build prompt using promptBuilder.js with: role definition + student level + mode-specific instructions + document context
•	4. Call Groq API and stream response to frontend via SSE
•	5. Save AI response to Conversation.messages[]
•	6. Handle student input differently per mode:
     - Teach Mode: Break it down, check understanding, move to next chunk
     - Explain Concepts: Holistic view, simplified analogies
     - Quiz/Exam: Evaluate immediately, update profile, do not re-explain unless asked
•	7. All interaction must be streamed via SSE for a word-by-word real-time experience

