📄  SECTION 11: DOCUMENT UPLOAD SYSTEM & RATE LIMITING
Large file handling, background queues, and daily enforcement

11.1 Upload Rate Limiting — PDF (2/day) & Images (5/day)
Every user is limited by file type per day. This is enforced at the middleware level.

Scenario	Limit	HTTP Response if Hit
PDF Upload	2 per user per day	429 Too Many Requests
Image Upload	5 per user per day	429 Too Many Requests
File Size	Max 50MB per file	413 Payload Too Large

11.2 Upload Limit Schema (MongoDB)
Tracked in the User document directly:

// Added to User model
pdfUploadCount:   { type: Number, default: 0 },
imgUploadCount:   { type: Number, default: 0 },
lastUploadDate:   { type: Date,   default: null },

// Middleware logic
const today = new Date().toDateString();
const isNewDay = user.lastUploadDate?.toDateString() !== today;

if (isNewDay) { 
  user.pdfUploadCount = 0; 
  user.imgUploadCount = 0; 
}

// Logic then checks file type and increments specific counter
// if (pdf) user.pdfUploadCount += 1;
// if (img) user.imgUploadCount += 1;

11.3 Document Handling — Background Queue
Large files are never processed synchronously. The API responds immediately and a background worker handles the heavy lifting.

File Size	Processing Strategy	User Experience
Under 5MB	Process inline — fast enough to not block	Ready in ~2 seconds
5MB – 50MB	Queue immediately via BullMQ — background worker processes	Sees 'Processing...' spinner, notified when ready
Over 50MB	Rejected at upload — file too large	Error message: 'Max file size is 50MB'
Unsupported	Rejected at Multer middleware	Error message: 'Only PDF and Image files are accepted'

